---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="9 Holidays I Wish I Had Never Been On | Christopher Hogg" description="A 425-page memoir exploring domestic violence, Cold War childhood, and whether AI can enhance understanding of trauma.">

  <!-- Hero Image -->
  <div class="w-full">
    <img src="/images/9-holidays-toys.jpg" alt="9 Holidays I Wish I Had Never Been On" class="hero-image" loading="eager" />
  </div>

  <section class="section-paper py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl">
      <a href="/projects" class="label text-gold hover:text-graphite transition-colors mb-8 inline-block">&larr; All Projects</a>

      <div class="accent-line mb-6" style="background-color: var(--color-holidays);"></div>
      <h1 class="heading-lg mt-4 mb-6">9 Holidays I Wish I Had Never Been On</h1>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-10">
        <span class="badge-outline">Memoir</span>
        <span class="badge-outline">AI Research</span>
        <span class="badge-outline">Substack</span>
        <span class="badge-outline">Palgrave</span>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-graphite leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-lg font-light">
          A weekly memoir published on Substack, spanning 425 pages, about surviving domestic violence and growing up in the shadow of the mushroom cloud during the 1980s.
        </p>

        <p>
          The project asks a radical question: <strong>what intelligence does trauma create?</strong> It explores whether a "virtual being" built from memoir text can enhance understanding of trauma, whether a virtual representation of one's childhood self, constrained in knowledge to a specific timeframe, can offer new therapeutic pathways.
        </p>

        <!-- Pull quote callout -->
        <blockquote class="pull-quote my-10" style="border-color: var(--color-holidays);">
          What intelligence does trauma create? Can a virtual representation of one's childhood self, constrained in knowledge to a specific timeframe, reveal something that unconstrained intelligence cannot?
        </blockquote>

        <h3 class="heading-md mt-12 mb-4">The AI Angle</h3>
        <p>
          At its heart, this project sits at the frontier of AI and life writing. Can artificial intelligence help us understand our own experiences differently? Can constraining an AI to the knowledge and perspective of a child, a specific child, in a specific time, reveal something that unconstrained intelligence cannot?
        </p>

        <h3 class="heading-md mt-12 mb-4">Academic Recognition</h3>
        <p>
          Invited by <strong>Palgrave "Studies in Life Writing"</strong> to submit a proposal for an 80,000-word experimental book expanding on this work.
        </p>

        <h3 class="heading-md mt-12 mb-4">Impact</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3 my-6 stagger">
          <div class="stat-card fade-in" style="--stat-bg: #D4760A; --stat-bg-end: #a05a08;">
            <p class="stat-number">425</p>
            <p class="stat-label">Pages</p>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card fade-in" style="--stat-bg: #D4760A; --stat-bg-end: #a05a08;">
            <p class="stat-number">328+</p>
            <p class="stat-label">Subscribers</p>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card fade-in" style="--stat-bg: #D4760A; --stat-bg-end: #a05a08;">
            <p class="stat-number">80k</p>
            <p class="stat-label">Palgrave Proposal</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="heading-md mt-12 mb-4">Read</h3>
        <div class="card border-l-holidays">
          <p class="text-ash mb-4">The memoir is published weekly on Substack and has 328+ subscribers.</p>
          <a href="https://christopherhogg.substack.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-dark">
            Read on Substack &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
